{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Pin down the apply-now vs defer-with-reason ranking rule with a concrete worked example.","decision":"block","finding_refs":["febacdc27cb5cf393","ffe0a05e876249faa","f644bd06bd8785ae7"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"the apply-now vs defer-with-reason ranking rule"},{"coaching":"Plan how aggregate two-bucket output schema compatibility will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"block","finding_refs":["f261487feb7a53f76","fefba3649218325e5","f1b650836e79cc5dd","f9a7b54f1348fa190"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"aggregate two-bucket output schema compatibility"},{"coaching":"Research prior art / OSS for remediation-mode carryover field in finding schema before building it custom.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f2f4366ccfa005372","fcc16ae31d41f0f95","f7b737a434c72a93b","f37a217969d654d26"],"move_id":"2","move_name":"prior-art research","subject":"remediation-mode carryover field in finding schema"},{"coaching":"Weigh at least one structural alternative for blocking findings as eligible triage triggers.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f9174f843964d5981","f7d746dbbd297c945","f28556c3934d15352","faff23e59768da780"],"move_id":"5","move_name":"weigh alternatives","subject":"blocking findings as eligible triage triggers"},{"coaching":"Run a quick pre-mortem on missing-input fallback for ranking computation: how could this plan fail?","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fe59e8e4937a035e2"],"move_id":"3","move_name":"pre-mortem","subject":"missing-input fallback for ranking computation"},{"coaching":"State the concrete attestation evidence the [operator-attested] authoritative MOVE_REGISTRY definition location will require (a change id / vote outcome / timestamp), recorded on the ticket.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fde109c20ee5a3e58"],"move_id":"14","move_name":"state attestation evidence","subject":"authoritative MOVE_REGISTRY definition location"},{"coaching":"Plan how acceptance-criteria completeness and measurability will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f607dd457c67f9209"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"acceptance-criteria completeness and measurability"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":13,"blocking":5,"dropped":5,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":4,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","ran":true,"references":0,"resolved":0,"status":"pass"},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":4,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":1827,"file_impact":3,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":0,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":4,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"fail","verify_commands_linted":0,"verify_lint_abstained":0},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":473,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P9":{"applicable":true,"blocking":false,"file_impact":3,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":318.7,"llm_calls":29,"llm_ms":482517.3,"total_ms":482984.9,"verify_requests":17},"remediation":{"baseline":"sidecar","eligible":false,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":false,"plan_changed":false,"registry_unchanged":false,"sidecar_baseline":false,"within_window":false}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["A1","E4","G1G2","G6","G7","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8","removal-rationale"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","E5","E6","F1","G5","T2","T4","T5a","T5b","T5e","T6","T7","T9","hedge"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] State the complete ranking rule in the plan body: specify the ordering/weighting among priority, criteria tier, and remediation-mode carryover status, and the threshold/condition that assigns an advisory to 'apply-now' vs 'defer-with-reason' — so the unit test in AC2 pins the intended rule, not an arbitrary implementation choice.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E2","E6","F1"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan body: 'ranks the round\\'s surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets using only recorded finding fields (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status) - no new LLM judgment'","AC2: 'the note orders advisories by the documented ranking rule, pinned by test' — the 'documented ranking rule' is referenced but never stated in this plan","ABSENCE: No tie-breaking rule, no weight/ordering between priority vs criteria tier vs carryover status, no threshold stated for 'apply-now' qualification"],"finding":"The ranking rule that determines 'apply-now vs defer-with-reason' assignment is never defined in the plan. The plan names the inputs (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status) but never specifies how they combine or which takes precedence, meaning the executor must design the algorithm themselves — a real design decision deferred rather than a defaultable gap.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"febacdc27cb5cf393","impact":0.8,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section ('apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets using only recorded finding fields (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status)') and AC2 ('orders advisories by the documented ranking rule, pinned by test')","norm_id":"n2a75fe8930426fa2","priority":0.8,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["Executor writes the ranking algorithm however seems natural, the pinned test reflects that arbitrary choice, and the move produces different triage results than the author intended.","Two engineers implement the move independently and produce byte-incompatible outputs — the determinism test only pins within one implementation, not across implementations."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Add a 'Ranking rule' subsection to the What or Scope section, e.g.: 'Sort surviving advisories by (1) priority descending, (2) criteria-tier severity descending, (3) remediation-mode carryover status (carried > new). An advisory is apply-now if priority ≥ HIGH or criteria-tier = blocking-tier; otherwise defer-with-reason. Ties broken by finding ID for determinism.' Then reference this exact rule in AC2.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"high"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Clarify whether the advisory-triage move is (a) a standard `{subject}`-template move that emits 'apply-now' or 'defer' coaching text per finding (no new rendering code), or (b) a collective ranking across all advisories (requires new rendering logic beyond the existing `render_coach_notes` per-finding loop) — and update the Scope accordingly.","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["review_kernel/coach.py `render_coach_notes`: iterates raw_notes, renders `move['template'].format(subject=subject)` — one note per finding","MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA requires each move to have a single `{subject}` placeholder","The plan says 'template-rendered like every registry move' but also says it 'ranks…into buckets' — these are incompatible unless the template itself outputs the ranking prose, which would require the subject validator and template to handle multi-finding aggregation"],"finding":"The plan describes the new move as ranking surviving advisories into 'apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets' — a collective, multi-finding output. The existing `render_coach_notes` / `coach_listing` mechanism renders one note per finding from a per-finding `{subject}` template. A move that produces a ranked triage of all advisories collectively does not fit the existing `MoveRegistry` schema (`{subject}` placeholder, per-finding) and would require new rendering logic — constituting behavioral CREATION beyond a registry addition.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f261487feb7a53f76","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'ranks the round's surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets'","norm_id":"n1eac492e5d2e302d","priority":0.7556,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["Implementer tries to add a new `MOVE_REGISTRY` entry with a standard template and discovers the per-finding rendering cannot produce a collective ranking without modifying `render_coach_notes` or `coach_listing`.","If implemented as a standard move, the 'ranking' claim is misleading — the move would produce one advisory note per finding, not a ranked triage list."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.8889,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"medium","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify how the advisory-triage move's two-bucket ranked output (apply-now / defer-with-reason) is rendered within the existing `{subject}`-only template constraint — either by reframing the move as a single set-level summary note (with a concrete example template), extending the template schema to support additional named placeholders, or describing a separate rendering path; the current plan leaves this gap unresolved.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["validate_move_registry in review_kernel/coach.py: 'if not isinstance(template, str) or \"{subject}\" not in template: raise ValueError' — every template must have exactly one {subject} placeholder","render_coach_notes: 'coaching': move['template'].format(subject=subject) — substitutes a single noun-phrase, not a multi-finding sorted bucket list","Plan: 'ranks the round's surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets' — a set-level two-bucket ordered output, structurally incompatible with a {subject} template per-finding render","ABSENCE: the plan never specifies what the template string looks like or how the bucket assignment is encoded within the {subject} constraint"],"finding":"The 'advisory-triage' move's intended output — a two-bucket ranked list of surviving advisories ('apply-now' vs 'defer-with-reason') — cannot be rendered by the existing {subject}-placeholder template schema that validate_move_registry enforces (raises if template lacks exactly one {subject}). A single noun-phrase substitution cannot produce an enumerated, ordered split across multiple finding ids. The plan says 'template-rendered like every registry move' and 'no new LLM judgment', but doesn't specify how a template that only accepts {subject} emits the described triage structure.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fefba3649218325e5","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section; AC line 1 ('The move renders deterministically from recorded finding fields')","norm_id":"n96d44a0ab82982db","priority":0.6375,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["Implementer adds a move with template 'Triage {subject}' — the subject is a noun phrase, not a bucket list; the triage ordering is lost entirely","Implementer tries to cram the bucket list into {subject} — violates the ≤8 words / ≤60 chars subject validator constraint","Implementer adds new template variables (e.g. {apply_now}, {defer}) — breaks validate_move_registry's {subject}-only invariant and requires schema extension not specified in the plan"],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"If the intent is a single set-level coaching note, the move's template could be: 'Triage {subject} before claiming: apply high-priority advisories now; record a one-line deferral rationale in the description for the rest.' The {subject} would be a noun-phrase like 'the N surviving advisories'. The bucket-ordering detail (which are apply-now vs defer) would then be implicit (apply the higher-priority ones), not enumerated in the template output. Alternatively, describe a new rendering hook that passes additional fields beyond {subject} — but that requires a schema change that should be called out explicitly.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"medium","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"medium","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Define the ranking rule explicitly in the plan (e.g. a table or formula mapping priority × criteria-tier × carryover-status → apply-now|defer-with-reason), so AC2's 'documented ranking rule' refers to something reviewable before implementation begins.","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'ranks the round's surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets using only recorded finding fields (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status)'","AC2: 'the note orders advisories by the documented ranking rule, pinned by test' — but the rule itself is never documented in the plan","Research baseline (R6 in task-decomposition-sota-2026.md §R6) describes a simpler trigger (≥N advisories → triage prompt) with no bucketing algorithm; the plan upgrades to a binary-bucket ranking not specified anywhere","ABSENCE: no formula, threshold, or ordering predicate appears in the plan text, Scope, or ACs"],"finding":"The 'apply-now vs defer-with-reason' ranking rule — the core novelty of this move — is never defined in the plan. The three inputs are named (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status) but no algorithm for combining them into buckets is specified. The deterministic/byte-identical claim in AC1 and the unit-test ordering pin in AC2 are unachievable without this rule being pinned; an implementer must invent it, introducing non-determinism at the plan level.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"ffe0a05e876249faa","impact":0.8,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section / AC1 ('same verdict -> byte-identical note') / AC2 ('orders advisories by the documented ranking rule, pinned by test')","norm_id":"n848878809c1101e5","priority":0.8,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["An implementer chooses a ranking rule (e.g. priority ≥ 0.6 = apply-now) that differs from what the author intended; the unit test pins the wrong rule; the feature ships with an unreviewed algorithm.","The 'documented ranking rule' AC2 references does not exist yet — if docs/plan-review-gate.md is where it gets documented (AC3), the plan creates a circular dependency: the rule must be authored during implementation with no prior specification to validate against."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Add a 'Ranking rule' subsection to the plan's What section. For example: 'apply-now if priority ≥ 0.5 OR criteria tier is blocking-eligible; defer-with-reason otherwise; remediation-mode carryover status (True/False per finding) breaks ties toward apply-now.' Pin the exact thresholds so the unit test is verifying a reviewed spec, not an implementer's choice.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"high"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Define the complete ranking rule for apply-now vs defer-with-reason assignment: specify the decision function over priority, criteria tier, and carryover status — including thresholds, ordering among the three inputs, and tie-breaking — co-located with the move definition or in a dedicated rule table in docs/plan-review-gate.md.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan 'What': 'ranks the round's surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets using only recorded finding fields (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status)'","AC2: 'the note orders advisories by the documented ranking rule, pinned by test'","No rule definition exists in the plan text — neither a formula, a threshold table, nor a decision tree mapping the three inputs to bucket assignments","Cached review finding confirms same gap: 'The ranking rule that determines apply-now vs defer-with-reason assignment is never defined in the plan'"],"finding":"The 'ranking rule' that assigns each advisory to 'apply-now' vs 'defer-with-reason' is never defined anywhere in the plan. The plan names three inputs (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status) but specifies no decision function — no thresholds, no ordering formula, no tie-breaking. AC2 requires the rule be 'documented' and 'pinned by test', yet a test can only pin a rule that is stated.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f644bd06bd8785ae7","impact":0.8,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section ('ranks the round's surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets using only recorded finding fields'); AC2 ('the note orders advisories by the documented ranking rule')","norm_id":"nef8dbb6ba0de037e","priority":0.8,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["An implementer reading the plan cannot write the deterministic ranking logic — any implementation is an invention, not a spec-faithful translation.","The AC2 test that 'pins the ranking rule' cannot be written without the rule; different engineers would write incompatible tests."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Add a rule table, e.g.: apply-now if (priority ≥ P_THRESHOLD) OR (criteria_tier == 'blocking-capable' AND carryover) else defer-with-reason. Specify P_THRESHOLD value, the enumeration of 'criteria tier' values, and what 'carryover status = true' means on a finding record.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"high"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Clarify whether the advisory-triage move is a per-finding label (fits the existing {subject} template contract) or a round-level aggregate note (requires a new render path not in the kernel); if per-finding, restate AC1 to match the per-finding template semantics.","cohort":["A1"],"criteria":["A1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["coach.py coach_listing: 'Emit one note per finding you can map to a useful move (skip findings no move fits)'","coach.py render_coach_notes: note = {..., 'coaching': move['template'].format(subject=subject)} — one prose string per note, keyed by a single {subject}","passes.py CoachNote schema: {move_id, subject, finding_refs} — per-finding, not per-round","Plan says 'ranks the round\\'s surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets' — implies a round-level aggregate note, not a per-finding template substitution","No aggregate-render path exists in review_kernel.coach or passes.py"],"finding":"The plan describes the triage move as ordering 'the round's surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets' — an aggregate/group output across multiple findings — but the existing template contract (review_kernel/coach.py render_coach_notes) is strictly per-finding: each CoachNote maps to one {subject} substitution, and coach_listing instructs 'Emit one note per finding you can map to a useful move.' Expressing a two-bucket ranking of all surviving advisories in a single locked template with a single {subject} placeholder is not possible without either bending the per-finding semantics or adding a new aggregate-render path that does not exist in the codebase, which would be an unplanned abstraction.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f1b650836e79cc5dd","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"## What / Acceptance Criteria AC1 ('the note orders advisories by the documented ranking rule')","norm_id":"n61fea2b7975d07b0","priority":0.7556,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["If the move is intended as a per-finding label ('apply this finding now' / 'defer this finding'), the {subject} template can express it but the 'ordering into buckets' framing is misleading and the AC ('the note orders advisories') is unsatisfiable by a single template substitution.","If the move is intended as a round-level summary across all findings, it requires a new render mechanism outside the locked template model, introducing unplanned complexity."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Reframe the move as a per-finding label: e.g., a template 'Apply {subject} in this session — priority warrants immediate action.' vs a separate move 'Defer {subject} to a follow-on ticket — lower priority.' Both fit the existing {subject} contract and together achieve the triage effect without a new render path.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.8889,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"medium","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.75,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Verify whether 'remediation-mode carryover status' is an existing field on surviving advisory finding dicts at pass-4 time (it is not in the current codebase — only dropped findings get `novelty`), and either correct the ranking-rule description to use an existing field or explicitly scope adding `novelty` to surviving findings as part of this work.","cohort":["E4"],"criteria":["E4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan quote: 'ranks the round's surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets using only recorded finding fields (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status)'","src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py line 104: only DROPPED findings get {**f, '_floored': True, 'novelty': nov, 'drop_reason': 'novelty'} — surviving findings in verdict['advisory'] carry no novelty/carryover field","src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/decide.py line 429: pass3_over_findings stamps decided findings with 'tier':'LLM' but no carryover/novelty field","ABSENCE: grep for 'carryover' in src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py and orchestrator.py returns zero hits; the carryover concept is the novelty SCORE, consumed internally by _apply_floor_to_verdict and never persisted onto surviving advisory findings"],"finding":"The plan asserts the advisory-triage move ranks advisories using 'remediation-mode carryover status' from 'recorded finding fields,' but surviving advisory findings at pass-4 time do NOT carry a carryover/novelty field in the current codebase.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f2f4366ccfa005372","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'no new LLM judgment, template-rendered … using only recorded finding fields (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status)'","norm_id":"nce0a9737171aad5b","priority":0.6611,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["When the implementer writes the deterministic ranking logic for the advisory-triage move, 'remediation-mode carryover status' will not be available on surviving finding dicts — the move will either silently treat all survivors as non-carryover or require a new field to be added, but neither is specified.","A unit test pinning 'byte-identical rendering from recorded finding fields' will fail if the test tries to use a novelty/carryover field that isn't present on surviving findings."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Replace 'remediation-mode carryover status' in the ranking rule with an existing finding field (e.g. `tier` which distinguishes DET vs LLM, or document that a `novelty` field must be carried forward onto surviving findings as in-scope work for this ticket).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7778,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"medium","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Verify that 'remediation-mode carryover status' is actually present on the finding dicts passed to Pass-4, or enumerate the propagation step needed to expose it (e.g., adding a `carryover` field in `partition_findings` or `pass3_over_findings`).","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["orchestrator.py `partition_findings`: surviving finding fields are `id`, `decision`, `severity`, `priority`, `validity`, `impact`, `tier`, plus Pass-1 fields (`finding`, `criteria`, `evidence`, etc.) — no `carryover` field","Search for 'carryover' in passes.py: no matches","sidecar.py line 308 comment: 'LOW novelty (\"carryover\")' — this is a sidecar-only label, not on the live finding dict","ABSENCE: no `carryover` key on finding objects in orchestrator.partition_findings or workflow_ops.plan_review_decide output"],"finding":"'Remediation-mode carryover status' is cited as one of the three recorded finding fields used for ranking, but this field is not present on the finding dicts that Pass-4 receives. The `partition_findings` output (`surfaced`, `blocking`) does not include a carryover field; carryover is a novelty-floor concept recorded in the sidecar but not propagated to the coach-facing finding objects.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fcc16ae31d41f0f95","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'using only recorded finding fields (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status)'","norm_id":"nce5daea21cca29c5","priority":0.6611,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Implementer writes deterministic ranking logic that reads `f.get('carryover_status')` on surviving findings and always gets `None`, silently producing a broken ranking."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7778,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"medium","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Confirm that 'remediation-mode carryover status' resolves to an existing per-finding field (cite the exact field name and where it is set), or explicitly scope the plan to include the schema extension needed to add it.","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'using only recorded finding fields (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status) — no new LLM judgment'","src/rebar/llm/plan_review/attest.py:182 — remediation_mode_candidate() is a ticket-level eligibility check returning {eligible, reasons}, not a per-finding attribute","src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py _pass1_model — finding fields are: finding, criteria, location, evidence, scenarios, impact, checklist_item, suggested_fix — no remediation_mode field","src/rebar/llm/plan_review/orchestrator.py partition_findings — minted finding fields: decision, severity, priority, validity, impact, tier — no remediation_mode_carryover field","ABSENCE: no search hit for 'remediation_mode' on individual finding dicts anywhere in the codebase"],"finding":"'Remediation-mode carryover status' is asserted as a per-finding recorded field available at deterministic render time, but no such field exists on individual findings in the codebase. The finding schema (passes.py _pass1_model, orchestrator.py partition_findings) carries no remediation-mode attribute; remediation_mode_candidate() in attest.py is a ticket-level re-review eligibility predicate, not a per-finding annotation. If this field must be added to the finding schema, that is an unspecified schema change with downstream attestation and sidecar implications.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f7b737a434c72a93b","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'using only recorded finding fields (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status)'","norm_id":"n68114843e35ec506","priority":0.6611,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer discovers the field doesn't exist and must either add it to the finding schema (a scope-expanding change not covered by this plan) or redefine 'carryover status' as something different — silently changing the move's behavior from what the plan describes.","If a schema extension is required, the attestation material fingerprint and sidecar format may need updates, cascading into signed-verdict backward-compatibility concerns outside this plan's scope."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7778,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"medium","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Reconcile the two-bucket aggregate output shape with the existing {subject}-template schema: either (a) redefine the move as a per-finding note that emits a bucket label as the subject (and show this satisfies AC2's ordering requirement), or (b) specify the schema extension needed to support aggregate/multi-finding templates and update MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA accordingly.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA (coach.py:35-58) defines moves as {name, template, applies_when} where template must contain a single {subject} placeholder","render_coach_notes (coach.py:162-196) calls move['template'].format(subject=subject) once per raw pick — a per-finding, single-sentence render","The plan's output ('apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets') is an aggregate over the full advisory list, not a per-finding sentence with a noun-phrase subject","C1 subject validator (coach.py:148-159) validates a bounded noun-phrase ≤8 words — incompatible with a bucket list output","Cached review finding confirms: 'The advisory-triage move's intended output — a two-bucket ranked list of surviving advisories — cannot be rendered by the existing {subject}-placeholder template mechanism'"],"finding":"The two-bucket aggregate output shape (a ranked list partitioned into apply-now / defer-with-reason across ALL surviving advisories) is structurally incompatible with the existing MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA and render path. Every existing registry move emits one coaching sentence per finding via template.format(subject=subject). The new move must produce an ordered cross-finding bucket list — a categorically different output — but the plan claims it is 'template-rendered like every registry move, subject to the existing C1 subject validator'.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9a7b54f1348fa190","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section ('template-rendered like every registry move'); Scope section (src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/coach.py); src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/coach.py:35-58 (MOVE_REGISTRY_SCHEMA), coach.py:162-196 (render_coach_notes)","norm_id":"ne783259cd2175e19","priority":0.6611,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer trying to add this as a standard registry entry cannot represent the bucket-list output in a {subject} template; they must either extend the schema (breaking the 'no new LLM judgment, template-rendered like every registry move' claim) or produce a per-finding note that doesn't achieve the triage goal.","The C1 subject validator would reject any subject string that tries to encode a bucket assignment ('advisories in apply-now bucket') as overlong or imperative."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7778,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"medium","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"medium","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify what 'remediation-mode carryover status' means as a per-finding field: either cite the existing finding field name and its schema location, or add it to the scope as a new field that must be stamped onto findings (with its source and propagation path defined).","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan 'What': 'using only recorded finding fields (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status)'","attest.remediation_mode_candidate() returns {'eligible': bool, 'reasons': {...}} — a ticket-level gate decision, not a per-finding field","passes.py MOVE_REGISTRY entries and render_coach_notes consume finding dicts; no finding schema in the codebase contains a 'carryover_status' or 'remediation_mode' field","The 'carryover' concept in __init__.py:198 refers to novelty-floor escape prevention, not a triage bucket input on findings","No schema definition (JSON Schema file or dataclass) in the plan or codebase defines 'carryover status' as a per-finding field"],"finding":"'Remediation-mode carryover status' is referenced as one of the three ranking inputs (a 'recorded finding field') but is not a field on individual advisory finding records in the existing schema. The codebase shows remediation_mode_candidate() returns a gate-level eligibility dict ({eligible, reasons}) — not a per-finding attribute — and no existing finding schema includes a carryover status field.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f37a217969d654d26","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section ('using only recorded finding fields (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status)');\nsrc/rebar/llm/plan_review/attest.py:182-210 (remediation_mode_candidate);\nsrc/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py:195-201 (surfaced_findings / carryover context)","norm_id":"nd641c9f61e238d2a","priority":0.6611,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer reading the plan cannot locate 'remediation-mode carryover status' on any finding record — the field does not exist where the plan claims it does.","The deterministic ranking rule (once defined) cannot be applied without this field; the move silently degrades to a two-input rule or requires a schema addition not specified in the plan."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7778,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"medium","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Clarify the move's output when triggered by a blocking finding but zero surviving advisories exist (e.g., 'emit a one-line note: no advisories to triage this round' or 'skip rendering entirely') so the executor and test author have a stated default.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC2: 'Blocking and advisory findings are both eligible triggers, and the note orders advisories by the documented ranking rule'","What section: 'ranks the round\\'s surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets'","ABSENCE: No statement of what the move emits when there are zero surviving advisories but one or more blocking findings"],"finding":"AC2 states 'Blocking and advisory findings are both eligible triggers' but the plan elsewhere describes the move as one that 'ranks the round\\'s surviving advisories' — it is ambiguous whether a round containing ONLY blocking findings (zero advisories) still runs the move and what output it produces, leaving the executor to decide behavior for this edge case.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9174f843964d5981","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC2 ('Blocking and advisory findings are both eligible triggers') vs. What section ('ranks the round\\'s surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets')","norm_id":"n9c43165995c6ac1e","priority":0.469,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A round has three blocking findings and no advisories; the move triggers (per AC2) but has nothing to rank — does it emit an empty note, skip rendering, or error? The executor must decide."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Add one sentence to the What section: 'If the triggering round contains blocking findings but no surviving advisories, the move renders a short note stating no advisories are eligible for triage this round (empty ranked list, still subject to C1 validator).'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Reconcile AC2's 'blocking findings are eligible triggers' with the parent epic's authoritative R6 rationale, which scopes this move to PASSING reviews only — either remove the blocking-finding trigger (narrowing to match the parent) or update the parent epic first to explicitly sanction firing on non-passing reviews before the leaf claims that scope.","cohort":["G7"],"criteria":["G7"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent epic (6982-2e75-f8fa-43b9) Context: 'R6 is the one deliberate exception: a deterministic pass-4 coaching move with no detection behavior ships first with no eval gate (validated by dogfooding via R7 metrics).'","Parent epic AC3: 'R6's terms are ship-first: deterministic rendering + validator compliance' — no mention of blocking-finding triggers.","Research doc §6 R6 (parent's authoritative source): 'Attach it whenever ≥N advisories survive on a PASSING review (N≈5).' A passing review has no blocking findings.","Leaf AC2: 'Blocking and advisory findings are both eligible triggers' — asserts a trigger class the parent's rationale explicitly excludes by scoping to passing reviews only."],"finding":"AC2 introduces 'Blocking findings' as eligible triggers for the advisory-triage move, but the parent's authoritative R6 rationale (§6 of the research doc the parent cites) scopes this move exclusively to PASSING reviews with surviving advisories ('whenever ≥N advisories survive on a passing review'). On a passing review, blocking findings cannot exist by definition — so the claim either implies the move fires on non-passing (blocked) reviews (outside the parent's scope) or is incoherent. The parent epic's normative ACs for R6 specify only 'deterministic rendering + validator compliance' and do not sanction this extension.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f7d746dbbd297c945","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC2 — 'Blocking and advisory findings are both eligible triggers'","norm_id":"n30919164da8804ac","priority":0.425,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["If the move is wired to fire on blocked reviews, it introduces behavior the parent never contemplated and could generate coaching noise on reviews that should be generating rework, not advisory triage.","If 'blocking findings eligible' is meant to say the move fires even when the round has surviving blockers (i.e., non-passing verdict), this diverges from the parent's 'pure coaching on a passing review' framing.","The pinned test in AC2 will lock in this extended trigger behavior, making it harder to realign to the parent's scope later."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Revise AC2 to read: 'The move fires on passing reviews where ≥N surviving advisories exist; the note orders advisories by the documented ranking rule, pinned by test.' If the intent is genuinely to also trigger on blocked reviews, update the parent epic first to add that scope, then re-review this leaf against the updated parent.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"low","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["2 criterion line(s) bundle multiple deliverables with 'and' (split so each is independently verifiable).","vague/subjective terms present: as needed"],"finding":"Acceptance-criteria / definition-of-done quality issues.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f607dd457c67f9209","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"ned06ebc801a522e3","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Split compound criteria, replace subjective terms with observable outcomes, and state how each is verified.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify the fallback behavior for the triage move when one or more ranking inputs (priority, criteria tier, carryover status) are null or missing on a finding — e.g., 'missing priority sorts as 0.0; missing tier defaults to lowest; missing carryover defaults to false' — and add a unit test pinning the degraded-input behavior.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan AC1: 'The move renders deterministically from recorded finding fields'","Existing priority field on findings defaults to 0.0 in some paths (passes.py:396, orchestrator.py:406/419) but 'criteria tier' and 'carryover status' have no defined null-handling","The existing coach mechanism has a fallback (validate_subject returns None → finding skipped), but no analogous fallback for a missing ranking input is specified for this new move","No plan section addresses what the move emits when < N advisories survive, when all inputs are null, or when the carryover field is absent"],"finding":"No fallback is specified for the triage move when ranking inputs are missing or null (e.g., a finding with no priority score, an undefined criteria tier, or an unavailable carryover status). The plan requires deterministic rendering but the deterministic path is silent on degraded inputs.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fe59e8e4937a035e2","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section; AC1 ('renders deterministically from recorded finding fields'); AC2 ('orders advisories by the documented ranking rule')","norm_id":"nc8025d245842c4b7","priority":0.335,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A review run on a ticket with unscored findings (e.g., pass-2 verify failure path at orchestrator.py:456) produces findings without priority; the triage move's deterministic path is undefined.","A finding from a project-extended criterion with no criteria tier mapping silently corrupts the bucket assignment."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Add a defaults table to the move definition: priority absent → 0.0 (consistent with existing convention at passes.py:396); criteria tier absent → 'standard'; carryover absent → False (conservative: treat as not carried over).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Reconcile AC2's 'Blocking and advisory findings are both eligible triggers' with the plan body's advisory-only framing: either drop blockers from AC2, or add a sentence to What explaining the blocker-trigger role and how it affects ranking output.","cohort":["COH","E1","T4"],"criteria":["COH","E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC2: 'Blocking and advisory findings are both eligible triggers'","Why: 'authors defer advisory findings because nothing tells them which are worth applying now'","What: 'ranks the round's surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets'","ABSENCE: no explanation in What or Why for why blockers are co-eligible or how they interact with the advisory-ranking logic"],"finding":"AC2 introduces 'Blocking findings' as eligible triggers, but the entire plan body (Why, What) frames the move exclusively around advisory triage. Nothing in the plan explains why blockers should trigger or be ordered by this advisory-triage move, creating a cross-section contradiction that would send the implementer in two directions.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f28556c3934d15352","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria AC2 vs. Why / What sections","norm_id":"n496fe630482a1e7a","priority":0.268,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Implementer adds blocker-trigger logic to satisfy AC2 but has no spec for what the move should output when only blockers are present.","Implementer ignores blockers to match the body description and AC2 fails review."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"If the intent is that the move fires whenever any findings exist (to ensure advisories are triaged even when blockers are present), say so explicitly in What: 'The move is triggered whenever findings of any severity are present; it operates on the advisory subset for ranking.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Resolve the contradiction between AC2 ('blocking and advisory findings are both eligible triggers') and the What section ('ranks the surviving advisories'): clarify whether blocking findings trigger the move (cause it to fire) but are excluded from triage buckets, or are included in the output — and update AC2 to make the firing condition and the triaged set explicit.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC2: 'Blocking and advisory findings are both eligible triggers, and the note orders advisories by the documented ranking rule'","What: 'ranks the round's surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets'","coach() in review_kernel/coach.py: 'coachable = list(blocking) + list(surviving)' — blocking findings already participate in coaching, but as must-fix items, not triage candidates","Blocking findings cannot be 'deferred with reason' — they gate the attestation"],"finding":"AC line 2 states 'Blocking and advisory findings are both eligible triggers' but the What section says the move 'ranks the round's surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets.' These are contradictory: blocking findings are not candidates for advisory triage (authors must remediate them unconditionally; there is no 'defer' option). The existing coach() already passes blocking findings as a separate argument (story 8086), but the triage semantics for blockers — should they appear in the bucket list, trigger the move but not be triaged, or be excluded — is undefined.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"faff23e59768da780","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC line 2 ('Blocking and advisory findings are both eligible triggers') vs What section ('ranks the round's surviving advisories')","norm_id":"nf199caed40b6dfd0","priority":0.268,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Implementer reads AC2 and includes blocking findings in the triage bucket list — authors see 'defer this blocker' which is incorrect","Implementer treats AC2 as 'blockers trigger the move to fire' but only triages advisories — valid interpretation, but the plan never states this explicitly"],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Revise AC2 to: 'The move fires when the round has at least one surviving advisory finding; blocking findings are eligible triggers (their presence raises urgency) but are not triaged — only advisories are ranked apply-now vs defer-with-reason, since blocking findings must be resolved unconditionally.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"medium","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Correct the Scope section to name `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py` (where `MOVE_REGISTRY` is defined at line 729) as the primary edit target, not `orchestrator.py` (which only re-exports it).","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["orchestrator.py line 87: `from .passes import MOVE_REGISTRY, load_move_registry  # noqa: E402,F401`","passes.py line 729: `MOVE_REGISTRY: dict[str, dict[str, Any]] = {`","`passes.py` is not listed in the Scope section"],"finding":"The Scope section names `orchestrator.py (MOVE_REGISTRY)` as the primary edit target, but `MOVE_REGISTRY` is defined in `passes.py` (line 729); `orchestrator.py` merely re-exports it (`from .passes import MOVE_REGISTRY`). The actual file to edit for adding a new move is `passes.py`, which is not listed in scope.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fde109c20ee5a3e58","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section: 'src/rebar/llm/plan_review/orchestrator.py (MOVE_REGISTRY)'","norm_id":"n575cc79fd4698a28","priority":0.165,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer edits `orchestrator.py` looking for the dict literal and cannot find it, wasting time or editing the wrong file."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Replace `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/orchestrator.py (MOVE_REGISTRY)` with `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py (MOVE_REGISTRY)` in the Scope section.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Either define R7 inline in AC3 (e.g., a parenthetical: 'R7 = the latency-tracking metrics task') or add a forward-reference to the relevant epic/task that defines it.","cohort":["COH","E1","T4"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC3: 'dogfood expectation (advisory-application latency observed via R7 metrics)'","ABSENCE: R7 is not defined in Why, What, Scope, or any other section of this plan"],"finding":"AC3 references 'R7 metrics' as the mechanism for observing advisory-application latency, but R7 is never defined or cross-referenced anywhere in the plan, making the criterion unverifiable from the plan text alone.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"ff882c2de70609113","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria AC3","norm_id":"n22f985b337d8d0ab","priority":0.165,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["A reviewer cannot assess whether AC3 is met without external knowledge of what R7 is.","An implementer writing the docs section doesn't know what to document about R7."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an explicit back-out strategy to the plan (e.g., 'revert the registry entry via a single-line patch; no data migration required') so the no-flag decision is accompanied by a reversibility statement, as T4 requires.","cohort":["COH","E1","T4"],"criteria":["T4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["What: 'Incorporated directly into the packaged registry (no flags)'","Why: 'carries no detection risk, so it ships first with no eval gate'","ABSENCE: no rollback strategy, feature-flag escape hatch, or back-out sequence described anywhere in the plan"],"finding":"The plan ships the new move unconditionally into the packaged registry with no rollback path. If the move produces noisy or incorrect output in production, there is no described mechanism to disable or back out the change short of a code revert.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc24525b2d33edcde","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section ('Incorporated directly into the packaged registry (no flags)') and AC4","norm_id":"n0b2f07d1157a3890","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["The move's ranking heuristic produces unhelpful or misleading notes for an unanticipated finding shape; ops has no knob to disable it without a full deploy cycle."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a one-sentence rollback note in Scope or AC4: 'Back-out: remove the registry entry and redeploy; no stored state or schema change is involved, making revert safe at any time.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Define the advisory ranking rule as a named, documented constant (or small config struct) rather than an inline template expression, so R7 metric feedback can drive targeted tuning without touching template internals.","cohort":["T2","T5e","T7"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'ranks the round's surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets using only recorded finding fields (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status)'","'advisory-application latency observed via R7 metrics' (AC-3) implies the ranking will be evaluated and potentially adjusted","No mention of an externalized config, constant registry, or tunable weight for the ranking rule"],"finding":"The ranking rule (priority, criteria tier, remediation-mode carryover status) is a business heuristic that the plan anticipates tuning via R7 metrics, yet the plan specifies no configurability mechanism — the rule appears hardcoded in the template/move definition.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f04cfb302020fe845","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section / Acceptance Criteria AC-1 / AC-2","norm_id":"n331608cbd364a661","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["R7 metrics reveal the ranking rule under-weights a criterion tier; engineer must find and edit the hardcoded template logic rather than updating a named constant or config entry","A future move variant needs a different ordering; no seam exists to swap the rule without touching template internals"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Introduce a `ADVISORY_RANKING_ORDER: tuple[str, ...] = ('priority', 'criteria_tier', 'remediation_mode_carryover')` constant (or equivalent small dataclass) in the move module, referenced by the template renderer, so the rule is a single-edit change when R7 data informs a reorder.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Resolve the scope of 'eligible triggers' in AC #2: either (a) clarify that blocking findings act only as a precondition gate (the note fires when any blocking finding is present and advisories exist), or (b) specify that only advisories are triggers, and remove 'Blocking and' from AC #2 — whichever matches the actual intended behavior.","cohort":["E3","G5","T6"],"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["What section: 'ranks the round's surviving advisories into apply-now vs defer-with-reason buckets'","AC #2: 'Blocking and advisory findings are both eligible triggers, and the note orders advisories by the documented ranking rule'","The ranking rule explicitly covers only advisories in the What section, yet AC #2 adds blocking findings as 'eligible triggers' with no explanation of what triggering means for a blocking finding in the triage output"],"finding":"AC #2 states 'Blocking and advisory findings are both eligible triggers' but the What section says the move 'ranks the round's surviving advisories' — it is unclear whether blocking findings are genuinely in scope for triggering or ordering the triage note, creating an ambiguity the implementer must resolve without a clear spec.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f715e91fe103a6c8d","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria #2 vs. What section","norm_id":"nb432a1faefa92832","priority":0.201,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["Implementer writes the move to trigger only when advisories are present, but a reviewer reads AC #2 and expects blocking findings to also trigger the note — the acceptance test will be ambiguous or contradictory","If blocking findings do trigger the move, should they appear in the output ranking? The plan gives no answer, making the unit test for AC #2 impossible to write without guessing"],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"If the intent is that the triage note fires regardless of whether the round has blocking findings (i.e., advisories are the sole trigger), rewrite AC #2 as: 'The note fires whenever surviving advisories exist, and orders them by the documented ranking rule, pinned by test.' If blocking findings are a gate (note only fires when there are also blockers), state that explicitly.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add explicit unit-test cases for (a) zero surviving advisories (assert the move emits nothing / a defined no-op note), and (b) a finding missing one or more ranking fields (priority, criteria-tier, carryover-status), asserting graceful fallback behavior rather than a crash or silent misrank.","cohort":["E5"],"criteria":["E5"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC1: 'unit test: same verdict -> byte-identical note'","AC2: 'the note orders advisories by the documented ranking rule, pinned by test'","ABSENCE: no mention of zero-advisory input, partially-populated finding records, or null-field handling in any AC or scope item"],"finding":"The unit tests described cover only the happy-path (advisories present, all ranking fields populated, deterministic render, ordering). No test work is specified for the empty-advisory case (zero surviving advisories after a round) or for findings with missing/null priority, criteria-tier, or remediation-mode carryover fields — the very fields the ranking rule depends on.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fe6a105396b4a0fbf","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria AC1–AC2 / Scope ('Unit tests pinning deterministic rendering + validator compliance')","norm_id":"ne9b79a6df1d66fbb","priority":0.099,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A round ends with no surviving advisories (all promoted or dismissed) — the move receives an empty list; undefined behavior could emit a malformed note or crash the coach seam.","An upstream pass emits a finding without a priority or criteria-tier field (e.g., a legacy or manually-injected finding); the ranking rule dereferencing those fields fails silently or raises."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"In the AC or Scope, add: 'Unit tests must cover: (a) empty advisory list → move emits a defined no-op (e.g., omitted section or explicit 'no advisories to triage' note); (b) finding with absent priority/tier fields → move falls back to documented default rank (e.g., lowest bucket) without raising.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"84dc5ef1a4d6e907","metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":318.7,"llm_calls":29,"llm_ms":482517.3,"total_ms":482984.9,"verify_requests":17},"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","regver":"b293b9a55de591cc","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"plan_review_result_v2","ticket_id":"5dac-c177-56ff-4af4","ticket_type":"story","verdict":"BLOCK","verified_at_sha":"527a6e7302543c1d7bcf67fd828d5a1e191f7406"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"REVIEW_RESULT","timestamp":1784250866382950001,"uuid":"9d22f463-1d28-4ae3-967c-7ebb851607bb"}